The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation at a Glance

 Paper mill blast kills seven

Dehra Dun (PTI): Seven persons died and two were critically 

injured when a tank containing chemicals exploded at a paper mill in Kashipur 

on Monday, police said.

 The blast occurred when a group of labourers were working inside a godown where the tank containing the inflammable chemicals was kept. 

 The seven died on the spot.

 The explosion was so powerful that it shattered nearby windowpanes, triggering panic in the area. 

 Kashipur is an industrial town in Uttaranchals Udham Singh Nagar district.

 The two injured were taken to a nearby hospital where doctors said their condition was serious.

 Operations at the paper mill were suspended after the explosion.

 SC stays seer case trial

New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has stayed a Pondicherry 

court trial in the Sankar Raman murder case in which seer Jayendra Saraswati is 

a prime accused. 

 The Pondicherry court shall not proceed with the trial of the case till further order, the court said.

 The pontiff had challenged a Madras High Court order allowing the Tamil Nadu government to continue with its own prosecutor in the case, which was shifted to the Pondicherry court on the directions of the Supreme Court.

 The apex court said the Tamil Nadu government has no business to go to Pondicherry to conduct the case. The Tamil Nadu government is no longer a prosecuting state, it said. 

 Debt tragedy

 Kanpur (PTI): A man strangled his seven-year-old daughter 

and later committed suicide in the Yogendra Vihar area of Kanpur after incurring 

losses in business on Sunday. 

 Ram Kumar, a 48-year-old tea salesman, was under a huge debt, police said.

 BSP sack

 Badaun (UP) (PTI): The Bahujan Samaj Party has expelled 

former MP D.P. Yadav on the charge of indiscipline. Yadav had recently at 

a public meeting... said his son Vikas would be a BSP candidate in the next Vidhan 

Sabha election, which amounted to indiscipline, senior BSP leader Naseemuddin 

Siddique said in a letter. 

 Accident deaths

 Sangareddy (PTI): Ten people died when the auto-rickshaw 

in which they were travelling collided head-on with a lorry on the Hyderabad-Mumbai 

highway in Andhra Pradeshs Medak district. 

The 

Uttar Pradesh government will raise the compensation paid to the families of the 

1984 anti-Sikh riot victims by seven to 10 times. Each of the families was so 

far paid Rs 50,000. 




